did.head: Collection Summary

corpname.part: Geography and Map Division, Library of Congress

did.abstract: This sub-collection of the Heezen-Tharp maps and papers collection contains some 4162 cartographic items and supporting materials that are related to Bruce Heezen and Marie Tharp's mapping of the Pacific Ocean floor. The item types include manuscript and published maps, soundings, reports, and other scientific data. The materials are stored offsite at Ft. Meade and must be requested advance of visiting the Geography and Map Reading Room.

acqinfo.head: Provenance
acqinfo.p: The materials were purchased by the Geography and Map Division throughout the 1990s.

processinfo.head: Processing History
processinfo.p: The collection was arranged and described by Gary North and Ryan Moore in 2010.

relatedmaterial.head: Related Material
relatedmaterial.p: The parent collection is the Heezen-Tharp maps and papers collection.

userestrict.head: Copyright Status
userestrict.p: Materials from the Heezen-Tharp collection: Pacific Ocean are governed by the Copyright Law of the United States (Title 17, U.S.C.) and other applicable international copyright laws.

accessrestrict.head: Access and Restrictions
accessrestrict.p: The Heezen-Tharp collection: Pacific Ocean collection is open to research. Researchers are advised to contact the Geography and Map Reading Room prior to visiting. Many collections are stored off-site and advance notice is needed to retrieve these items for research use.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Researchers wishing to cite this collection should include the following information: Container number, Heezen-Tharp collection: Pacific Ocean collection, Geography and Map Division, Library of Congress, Washington, D.C.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Content Note
scopecontent.p: Consists of some 4162 items related to Heezen and Tharp's mapping of the Pacific Ocean floor.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: Important note: Each Group has a corresponding Holdings Number that can be located in Voyager by Library staff members. Item(s) filed within each Group have a corresponding Barcode number that Library staff members can locate in Voyager to retrieve it from Ft. Meade.
Some Groups or titles within Groups are labeled n/a. These items either were anticipated for acquisition in early processing stages or discarded at a later stage.
The Heezen-Tharp collection: Pacific Ocean is organized in four series:

list.item: Series II: Pacific Ocean Special Projects: Groups 24 - 32
Series III: Pacific Ocean Geologic Map: Groups 33 - 42
Series IV: Pacific Ocean Boxed Materials: Groups 43 - 45

controlaccess.head: Selected Search Terms
controlaccess.p: The following terms have been used to index the description of this collection in the LC Catalog. They are grouped by name of person or organization, by subject or location, and by occupation and listed alphabetically.

a. Paper. b. 00199, 18 July 1967. Covers 1706S. “1st attempt to computerize soundings, published in our 8x11 book w/ positives and scale depths given. In order to use these profiles, these sheets had to be glued together to make a continuous profile of the area across which the ship went. The profiles also had to have spot depths with peaks and valleys read off in uncorrected fathoms. These depths were then plotted on a map along the track, then they could be compared with other ship’s profiles which had also been plotted at a vertical exaggeration of 100:1. Many published volumes of this project went on to Colorado.”
